  "text": "Security audit of the Grafana observability stack identified critical HTTP endpoints registered without authentication middleware across both Loki and Mimir repositories.\n\n## Findings Summary\n\n### sg-benchmarks/grafana-loki\n\n**File: cmd/logql-analyzer/main.go (Lines 49, 53-55, 57)**\nThe LogQL analyzer command-line tool registers multiple unprotected HTTP endpoints without authentication middleware:\n- `/api/logql-analyze` (POST) - LogQL query analysis endpoint\n- `/api/sizing/helm` (GET) - Helm configuration sizing endpoint  \n- `/api/sizing/nodes` (GET) - Node sizing calculation endpoint\n- `/api/sizing/cluster` (GET) - Cluster sizing calculation endpoint\n- `/ready` (GET) - Readiness probe endpoint\n\nOnly CORS middleware is applied via `logqlanalyzer.CorsMiddleware()`, with no authentication or tenant validation.\n\n**File: pkg/loki/modules.go (Lines 247, 366, 652, 1290, 1400, 1456, 1579, 1696, 1781)**\nMultiple ring and cluster management endpoints are registered on the public HTTP server without authentication middleware:\n- `/ring` (GET, POST) - Ingester ring status endpoint\n- `/distributor/ring` (GET, POST) - Distributor ring status endpoint\n- `/pattern/ring` (GET, POST) - Pattern ingester ring status endpoint\n- `/ruler/ring` (GET, POST) - Ruler ring status endpoint\n- `/memberlist` - Memberlist cluster membership endpoint\n- `/compactor/ring` (GET, POST) - Compactor ring status endpoint\n- `/indexgateway/ring` (GET, POST) - Index gateway ring status endpoint\n- `/scheduler/ring` (GET, POST) - Query scheduler ring status endpoint\n- `/partition-ring` (GET, POST) - Partition ring status endpoint\n\nThese endpoints are registered directly on `t.Server.HTTP` without being wrapped with `t.HTTPAuthMiddleware` or any other authentication middleware. In contrast, properly protected endpoints like query and push operations use middleware wrapping (e.g., `httpMiddleware.Wrap()`).\n\n### sg-benchmarks/grafana-mimir\n\n**File: pkg/api/api.go (RegisterRoute calls with auth=false)**\nThe Mimir API registration layer has 50+ endpoints registered with the `auth` parameter set to `false`, meaning they do not require authentication:\n\n**Alertmanager endpoints:**\n- `/multitenant_alertmanager/status` (GET)\n- `/multitenant_alertmanager/configs` (GET)\n- `/multitenant_alertmanager/ring` (GET, POST)\n\n**Status and configuration endpoints:**\n- `/config` (GET)\n- `/` (GET) - Index page\n- `/static/*` (GET) - Static files\n- `/debug/fgprof` (GET) - Flamegraph profiling\n- `/api/v1/status/buildinfo` (GET)\n- `/api/v1/status/config` (GET)\n- `/api/v1/status/flags` (GET)\n- `/runtime_config` (GET)\n\n**Ring and cluster management endpoints:**\n- `/distributor/ring` (GET, POST)\n- `/ingester/ring` (GET, POST)\n- `/ingester/partition-ring` (GET, POST)\n- `/ruler/ring` (GET, POST)\n- `/store-gateway/ring` (GET, POST)\n- `/compactor/ring` (GET, POST)\n\n**Operational endpoints:**\n- `/distributor/all_user_stats` (GET)\n- `/distributor/ha_tracker` (GET)\n- `/ingester/flush` (GET, POST)\n- `/ingester/prepare-shutdown` (GET, POST, DELETE)\n- `/ingester/prepare-partition-downscale` (GET, POST, DELETE)\n- `/ingester/prepare-instance-ring-downscale` (GET, POST, DELETE)\n- `/ingester/unregister-on-shutdown` (GET, PUT, DELETE)\n- `/ingester/shutdown` (POST)\n- `/ingester/tenants` (GET)\n- `/ingester/tsdb/{tenant}` (GET)\n- `/ruler/rule_groups` (GET)\n- `/ruler/tenants` (GET)\n- `/ruler/tenant/{tenant}/rule_groups` (GET)\n- `/store-gateway/tenants` (GET)\n- `/store-gateway/tenant/{tenant}/blocks` (GET)\n- `/store-gateway/prepare-shutdown` (GET, POST, DELETE)\n\nThese endpoints are registered via the `RegisterRoute()` function with the third parameter (auth) set to `false`, explicitly indicating no authentication requirement.\n\n## Risk Assessment\n\nThe unprotected endpoints expose sensitive operational information:\n- Ring status endpoints reveal internal cluster topology, node distribution, and health state\n- Memberlist endpoint exposes cluster membership and node identities\n- Operational endpoints allow direct control over component shutdown and configuration\n- User-scoped endpoints like `/ingester/tsdb/{tenant}` may expose tenant-specific operational data\n\nThese should be protected with the same authentication middleware (`middleware.AuthenticateUser` in Loki, or `auth=true` in Mimir) applied to other sensitive endpoints."
